אבשׁלום    אבישׁלום / 'ăbîyshâlôm  'abshâlôm / ab-ee-shaw-lome', ab-shaw-lome'
=== Etymology ===

From [[אב]] {{HH|1}} and [[שׁלום]] {{HH|7965}}; 
=== Proper noun ===
father of peace (that is, friendly); [[Abshalom]], a son of [[David]]; also (the fuller form) a later Israelite: - Abishalom, Absalom.